01:28:30.400 --> 01:28:36.720
to be able to dream
these big dreams while--

01:28:36.720 --> 01:28:41.880
well, they don't pay their
employees as much as we would

01:28:41.880 --> 01:28:43.890
like to see them paid,
or we have a system

01:28:43.890 --> 01:28:48.510
where people aren't benefiting
from the labor that they put in,

01:28:48.510 --> 01:28:52.190
or are devalued and not--

01:28:52.190 --> 01:28:54.340
so being commodified
has a certain edge

01:28:54.340 --> 01:28:56.630
but being not a commodity
in terms

01:28:56.630 --> 01:28:59.250
of labor also has another edge.

01:28:59.250 --> 01:29:02.190
So to think about ethics
and economics together is

01:29:02.190 --> 01:29:04.730
to question if whether
the system we're

01:29:04.730 --> 01:29:08.010
in will produce just results.

01:29:09.370 --> 01:29:10.670
&gt;&gt; Lucianne Walkowicz: Yeah.

01:29:10.670 --> 01:29:11.970
I think also in terms of--

01:29:11.970 --> 01:29:15.580
since you brought up
