01:38:59.620 --> 01:39:02.400
with brilliant minds and
I love to just, you know,

01:39:02.400 --> 01:39:04.100
learn and kind of soak in.

01:39:04.100 --> 01:39:10.990
So I wrote a few pieces, kind
of related to my experience here

01:39:10.990 --> 01:39:14.200
on earth, because I think
a lot of the times we look

01:39:14.200 --> 01:39:20.210
out elsewhere and thinking about
colonizing and/or you know,

01:39:20.210 --> 01:39:22.650
moving on to new planets.

01:39:22.650 --> 01:39:26.840
Or we tend to look outward
at a lot of the problems

01:39:26.840 --> 01:39:28.950
and whatever is going
on within society.

01:39:28.950 --> 01:39:31.920
We look at, well this is the
problem [inaudible] a lot

01:39:31.920 --> 01:39:33.220
of the times.

01:39:33.220 --> 01:39:34.900
Whatever's going on within
society are all reflections

01:39:34.900 --> 01:39:37.810
of something that's
happening within us.

01:39:37.810 --> 01:39:40.350
So I think that our, the
key is actually to turn

01:39:40.350 --> 01:39:42.580
and look inward opposed
to outward.

01:39:42.580 --> 01:39:45.170
So I wrote something
kind of in the spirit,

01:39:45.170 --> 01:39:51.470
it's called Visitors,
story time by the way.

01:39:51.470 --> 01:39:54.430
So I'm hanging with a
few friends in a park,

01:39:54.430 --> 01:39:58.420
not going to lie, couple of them
are inebriated I don't know,

01:39:58.420 --> 01:39:59.810
this may or may not
have anything to do

01:39:59.810 --> 01:40:01.710
with the next part of the story.

01:40:01.710 --> 01:40:05.460
But we see this UFO,
we freak out a bit,

01:40:05.460 --> 01:40:09.130
we wonder if it's real, our
eyes are glued to it as it moves

01:40:09.130 --> 01:40:11.670
without making a sound.

01:40:11.670 --> 01:40:15.470
It lands softly in front
of us, the door opens,

01:40:15.470 --> 01:40:19.960
smog pours out the entrance,
and a silhouette appears.

01:40:19.960 --> 01:40:22.960
A voice speaks to us, not
aloud, but in our minds,

01:40:22.960 --> 01:40:25.260
it says that they are
communicating telepathically

01:40:25.260 --> 01:40:28.440
and that they are from
a galaxy far, far, away.

01:40:28.440 --> 01:40:33.410
And they're here to conduct
a study, they have questions,

01:40:33.410 --> 01:40:36.300
they have been listening
in on humanity for a while,

01:40:36.300 --> 01:40:40.550
long enough to be
confused, very confused.

01:40:40.550 --> 01:40:43.640
They ask can we help to clarify.

01:40:43.640 --> 01:40:44.940
They understand some
of the words

01:40:44.940 --> 01:40:49.180
but not the feeling behind them,
not the humanness behind them.

01:40:49.180 --> 01:40:51.080
Not the true experience
of being human,

01:40:51.080 --> 01:40:53.540
so they ask, can we help them.

01:40:53.540 --> 01:40:55.690
And I say yes.

01:40:55.690 --> 01:40:58.700
They ask me to explain love.

01:40:58.700 --> 01:41:00.500
I say I don't know
exactly what it is,

01:41:00.500 --> 01:41:02.330
but I know it's in our core.

01:41:02.330 --> 01:41:05.550
We can explain it biologically
but that's not the fun part.

01:41:05.550 --> 01:41:07.020
I say the really amazing part is

01:41:07.020 --> 01:41:09.300
when you see it in
action between us.

01:41:09.300 --> 01:41:12.740
When you see us give a shirt
off the back, off our own back

01:41:12.740 --> 01:41:16.730
for another, when you see us
greet a stranger with open arms,

01:41:16.730 --> 01:41:19.720
as if they were family, when
you see a person so engulfed

01:41:19.720 --> 01:41:21.980
in another that they bond
to the best of their ability

01:41:21.980 --> 01:41:23.670
for the rest of eternity.

01:41:23.670 --> 01:41:28.090
They stop me there and ask,
well then what is hate?

01:41:28.090 --> 01:41:30.640
I say I don't know exactly.

01:41:30.640 --> 01:41:33.200
But it seems like
it is in our core.

01:41:33.200 --> 01:41:35.200
It may be a leftover
from tribalism,

01:41:35.200 --> 01:41:37.330
manifesting in a modern way.

01:41:37.330 --> 01:41:40.230
Some think it's deeper and tied
to the meaning of our existence.

01:41:40.230 --> 01:41:42.860
It's painful to see it
in action between us,

01:41:42.860 --> 01:41:45.750
it shows up in the form of
violence, phobias, prejudice,

01:41:45.750 --> 01:41:48.430
racism, sexism, intolerance
between people

01:41:48.430 --> 01:41:51.070
that don't look like us.

01:41:51.070 --> 01:41:54.260
And even worse sometimes
the ones that do.

01:41:54.260 --> 01:41:57.400
With too much of it we boil over
from the pressure of negativity,

01:41:57.400 --> 01:42:00.600
usually from a place of hurt.

01:42:00.600 --> 01:42:05.440
Then they proceed to
ask me, what is loss?

01:42:05.440 --> 01:42:08.200
I say it's one of the
hardest things to cope with,

01:42:08.200 --> 01:42:11.690
we lose our family and friends
to time, they all pass away,

01:42:11.690 --> 01:42:14.880
and so will we but until you do
you have to process every bit

01:42:14.880 --> 01:42:17.570
of loss that you have taken on.

01:42:17.570 --> 01:42:20.810
Sometimes we lose so
much that we forgive,

01:42:20.810 --> 01:42:23.390
that we forget what
it is like to have.

01:42:23.390 --> 01:42:25.150
Where sometimes,
so much is taken

01:42:25.150 --> 01:42:29.420
that we forget what we deserve
to have in the first place.

01:42:29.420 --> 01:42:32.090
They ask me what is happiness?

01:42:32.090 --> 01:42:35.760
I say I'm not sure if
I've ever really known it.

01:42:35.760 --> 01:42:37.370
Let's say it may be temporary

01:42:37.370 --> 01:42:40.320
and maybe that's what
makes it so special.

01:42:40.320 --> 01:42:43.850
Knowing that loss is
omnipresent, still finding a way

01:42:43.850 --> 01:42:47.480
to be present enough to enjoy
our bodies in this space,

01:42:47.480 --> 01:42:51.160
our stories, smiling whether
it's for a reason or not,

01:42:51.160 --> 01:42:54.520
and not as a front but because
something inside us gives us

01:42:54.520 --> 01:42:58.030
permission; permission
to be okay,

01:42:58.030 --> 01:43:01.250
permission to experience bliss.

01:43:01.250 --> 01:43:04.010
They ask me what is destiny?

01:43:04.010 --> 01:43:06.950
I say it's wherever
we are headed.

01:43:06.950 --> 01:43:09.470
We feel like we know and we
think that it will be positive

01:43:09.470 --> 01:43:11.870
but we have no idea
where this will lead.

01:43:11.870 --> 01:43:14.390
The universe does not owe
us a fairy tale ending

01:43:14.390 --> 01:43:17.720
and that's why we must be
so careful in this moment.

01:43:17.720 --> 01:43:22.480
AI is just a step away, our feet
will soon land on Martian soil,

01:43:22.480 --> 01:43:24.290
tension is high across nations

01:43:24.290 --> 01:43:26.760
and across the globe our
children are forgetting

01:43:26.760 --> 01:43:29.580
about a world without screens.

01:43:29.580 --> 01:43:32.540
Attention spans are decreasing
but attention is being brought

01:43:32.540 --> 01:43:34.650
to the ugliest pieces
of who we are,

01:43:34.650 --> 01:43:38.240
a brutal truth of our essence.

01:43:38.240 --> 01:43:42.480
So lastly they ask
me, what is hope?

01:43:42.480 --> 01:43:45.580
And do I have it?

01:43:45.580 --> 01:43:51.400
Hope is like I guess I first
have to start with who I am,

01:43:51.400 --> 01:43:54.770
I am a product of love that
my mother and father had

01:43:54.770 --> 01:43:56.910
for one another, their
relationship crumbled

01:43:56.910 --> 01:43:59.950
but it never transpired
to the point of hate.

01:43:59.950 --> 01:44:03.980
They lost each other and I
grew up in a lost period where,

01:44:03.980 --> 01:44:07.450
as a lost boy in a scary world,
doing my best to find a way

01:44:07.450 --> 01:44:10.990
to be happy, understanding
that it's just as important

01:44:10.990 --> 01:44:12.930
to experience happiness
and sadness

01:44:12.930 --> 01:44:17.020
and that my personal destiny
is tied to our collective story

01:44:17.020 --> 01:44:18.820
in a way that hopefully
gives promise

01:44:18.820 --> 01:44:20.660
to our collective future.

01:44:20.660 --> 01:44:22.980
So do I have hope?

01:44:22.980 --> 01:44:25.240
I am hope, we all are.

01:44:25.240 --> 01:44:30.280
And although I cannot be sure
that we will figure it all

01:44:30.280 --> 01:44:35.310
out between us, at least I know
that there is hope inside of us.

01:44:35.310 --> 01:44:38.460
They stared deeply at us,
not just me and my friends

01:44:38.460 --> 01:44:41.060
at the park, but they
looked deeply in my eyes

01:44:41.060 --> 01:44:46.920
as if they were looking into our
entire species, and they say,

01:44:46.920 --> 01:44:49.340
that's all we need to know.

01:44:49.340 --> 01:44:53.150
Without a name, a
goodbye, or another word,

01:44:53.150 --> 01:44:58.200
they closed the door, the ship
silently rose, and they left.

01:44:58.200 --> 01:44:59.500
I hope it mattered.

01:44:59.500 --> 01:45:00.800
That's that piece.

