02:59:35.160 --> 02:59:39.330
I think for me the exploration
that kind of keys for it

02:59:39.330 --> 02:59:43.150
as far as-- and I work really
in robotic exploration,

02:59:43.150 --> 02:59:46.580
is I think of it
mostly as a kind of way

02:59:46.580 --> 02:59:49.780
of reflecting upon ourselves,
you know, there is sort

02:59:49.780 --> 02:59:53.020
of an inherent curiosity
to me, of course,

02:59:53.020 --> 02:59:56.290
about whether we're
alone in the universe.

02:59:56.290 --> 02:59:58.810
Statistically speaking I would
say it seems very unlikely

02:59:58.810 --> 03:00:01.850
but there was sort of sense of
looking at these other places

03:00:01.850 --> 03:00:05.150
as reflections upon like how did
we-- what is our origin story?

03:00:05.150 --> 03:00:06.450
How did we arrive here?

03:00:06.450 --> 03:00:08.490
How does a place
like Earth form?

03:00:08.490 --> 03:00:11.910
What is the context for
life showing up like ours?

03:00:11.910 --> 03:00:16.070
Mars is in so many ways
are very obvious reflection

03:00:16.070 --> 03:00:18.540
and from the fact that
when we see pictures of it,

03:00:18.540 --> 03:00:19.840
we can imagine ourselves there.

03:00:19.840 --> 03:00:22.140
We can-- there is a gravity
that's similar to ours,

03:00:22.140 --> 03:00:24.360
there was, you know, a warmer
weather environment in the past.

03:00:24.360 --> 03:00:26.010
There's still a lot of things.

03:00:26.010 --> 03:00:28.750
As inhospitable as Mars is
there are far more, you know,

03:00:28.750 --> 03:00:31.150
inhospitable places
in our solar system.

03:00:31.150 --> 03:00:34.530
So there is a fair amount of
ability to sort of reflect

03:00:34.530 --> 03:00:36.730
on our own planet like
kind of hope that some

03:00:36.730 --> 03:00:39.440
of these are opportunities
to do that I think.

03:00:39.440 --> 03:00:41.440
Yeah, there are most
powerful images of course

03:00:41.440 --> 03:00:44.480
of space [inaudible] are
often the once that show earth

03:00:44.480 --> 03:00:45.780
in the context of the places

03:00:45.780 --> 03:00:47.920
that we're visiting whether
the Earth on the horizon,

03:00:47.920 --> 03:00:52.440
Mars or the [inaudible]
picture from the voyagers.

03:00:52.440 --> 03:00:56.240
So I do sort of see them as
a way of looking at ourselves

03:00:56.240 --> 03:00:57.790
and being introspective.

03:00:57.790 --> 03:01:00.790
And I hope that many of
the people who continue

03:01:00.790 --> 03:01:04.630
to do this will also see that
as a motivating factor for this.

03:01:04.630 --> 03:01:09.800
