03:11:52.770 --> 03:11:55.260
&gt;&gt; I was wondering, why Mars?

03:11:55.260 --> 03:11:57.150
Why not colonize the moon

03:11:57.150 --> 03:12:00.880
or some independent
free floating habitat?

03:12:00.880 --> 03:12:07.110
&gt;&gt; Nathalie Cabro: Well,
I'll go first then you guys.

03:12:07.110 --> 03:12:10.450
Well, I think we are
going back to the moon.

03:12:10.450 --> 03:12:14.720
And frankly as a scientist I
think this is an excellent idea.

03:12:14.720 --> 03:12:16.360
This is next to home.

03:12:16.360 --> 03:12:19.490
This is a place where we
can learn a lot about how

03:12:19.490 --> 03:12:22.490
to do things right which
basically we'll be messing

03:12:22.490 --> 03:12:25.110
up a lot before we learn
how to make things right

03:12:25.110 --> 03:12:27.690
but it's closer to home,
so maybe the repercussions

03:12:27.690 --> 03:12:29.930
of that will be lesser.

03:12:29.930 --> 03:12:34.700
And there are also different
layers to that question.

03:12:34.700 --> 03:12:37.800
I would say that the
moon makes a lot of sense

03:12:37.800 --> 03:12:43.130
to try technologies, habitat
and the number of things.

03:12:43.130 --> 03:12:46.730
As far as why Mars,
then you go back maybe

03:12:46.730 --> 03:12:48.460
astrobiology question.

03:12:48.460 --> 03:12:54.170
And Mars is really about,
you know, this connection

03:12:54.170 --> 03:13:00.010
that we seem to have, you
know, we have had for so long.

03:13:00.010 --> 03:13:02.780
Mars makes humanity dream.

03:13:02.780 --> 03:13:05.130
It was first, the
agreement which turn

03:13:05.130 --> 03:13:06.430
out they are not there.

03:13:06.430 --> 03:13:07.780
The [inaudible] of
Mars, et cetera.

03:13:07.780 --> 03:13:10.210
Why? Because when you are
looking at the landscape

03:13:10.210 --> 03:13:14.070
of Mars you don't need
to invent any vocabulary

03:13:14.070 --> 03:13:15.850
to describe the landscapes.

03:13:15.850 --> 03:13:17.150
You have mountains.

03:13:17.150 --> 03:13:18.450
You have sunset.

03:13:18.450 --> 03:13:19.750
You have sunrises.

03:13:19.750 --> 03:13:21.050
You have valleys.

03:13:21.050 --> 03:13:22.350
You have [inaudible]
and dunes and wind.

03:13:22.350 --> 03:13:24.520
This is how we describe Earth.

03:13:24.520 --> 03:13:28.130
It's Earth that's dry
now on and, you know,

03:13:28.130 --> 03:13:30.610
at least less alive than we are.

03:13:30.610 --> 03:13:33.310
We don't know if there is
life actually out there

03:13:33.310 --> 03:13:37.070
but the fact is that early
Mars was fairly close--

03:13:37.070 --> 03:13:38.620
was not the same
but fairly close

03:13:38.620 --> 03:13:40.300
to what we know early Earth was.

03:13:40.300 --> 03:13:46.450
And if there is life somewhere
in the Solar System that's close

03:13:46.450 --> 03:13:50.790
to what we are at least in
theory, Mars would be the place.

03:13:50.790 --> 03:13:52.790
And there is something
that I really like that,

03:13:52.790 --> 03:13:54.490
I repeat all the time.

03:13:54.490 --> 03:13:57.260
There is something
special about Mars.

03:13:57.260 --> 03:14:00.390
And I still, as an
astrobiologist,

03:14:00.390 --> 03:14:02.550
don't know if there
is really a transition

03:14:02.550 --> 03:14:06.420
between what we called prebiotic
chemistry or I mean a line

03:14:06.420 --> 03:14:08.240
between prebiotic
chemistry and life,

03:14:08.240 --> 03:14:10.170
I really think there
is a transition

03:14:10.170 --> 03:14:12.000
that could, you know, that can.

03:14:12.000 --> 03:14:17.320
But what I know is that
our planet is so dynamic

03:14:17.320 --> 03:14:21.370
that whatever habits between
those two states of matter

03:14:21.370 --> 03:14:25.510
and something else is not
recorded anymore on our planet.

03:14:25.510 --> 03:14:26.810
It's gone.

03:14:26.810 --> 03:14:29.940
Erosion, it's-- to
plate tectonics.

03:14:29.940 --> 03:14:33.170
This record is gone, which
means that if we want

03:14:33.170 --> 03:14:37.440
to understand how life
started, what's the process,

03:14:37.440 --> 03:14:41.720
we are not going to find it
necessarily in our own planet.

03:14:41.720 --> 03:14:44.260
So, now you have to imagine
being an orphan and trying

03:14:44.260 --> 03:14:46.540
to figure out who
your parents are.

03:14:46.540 --> 03:14:48.390
They are gone, all right?

03:14:48.390 --> 03:14:52.420
So, where you go to, you
go to your, next of kin,

03:14:52.420 --> 03:14:55.590
aunt and uncle or, you
know, somebody close to you.

03:14:55.590 --> 03:14:57.140
Mars is that.

03:14:57.140 --> 03:15:01.550
And there is another plate
tectonic, the erosion is less,

03:15:01.550 --> 03:15:05.080
geology collectivity
is lesser on Mars too.

03:15:05.080 --> 03:15:07.830
And there are very, very,
very old rocks on Mars

03:15:07.830 --> 03:15:10.010
and that was still
exposed at the surface.

03:15:10.010 --> 03:15:11.360
Just because of panspermia,

03:15:11.360 --> 03:15:14.000
because of planetary exchange
there is a good chance

03:15:14.000 --> 03:15:17.520
that the same material
that created life

03:15:17.520 --> 03:15:20.640
on Earth maybe somewhere
on Mars.

03:15:20.640 --> 03:15:22.300
And it may be that Mars is going

03:15:22.300 --> 03:15:26.380
to be the place gives us a
response to, you know, how life,

03:15:26.380 --> 03:15:29.550
our own life formed, how
we got started, who we are.

03:15:29.550 --> 03:15:32.070
So, this is what's
special about Mars.

03:15:32.070 --> 03:15:33.590
This is the why behind Mars.

03:15:33.590 --> 03:15:38.490
This is the why beyond at least
the astrobiology part of it.

03:15:38.490 --> 03:15:42.370
As for the human part of
it, I think this is the--

03:15:42.370 --> 03:15:46.210
our old story of explaining
from going to, you know,

03:15:46.210 --> 03:15:47.780
a rock to the next rock,

03:15:47.780 --> 03:15:50.300
to the next continent
to the next ocean.

03:15:50.300 --> 03:15:54.200
It happens so that the next
rock is 50 million miles away

03:15:54.200 --> 03:15:55.500
from here.

03:15:55.500 --> 03:15:59.700
